  "prompt": "How can I stop thinking about my ex?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help you move on:\n\n1. Limit contact completely\n\u2022 Block/unfollow on social media\n\u2022 Delete their contact information\n\u2022 Avoid places they frequent\n\n2. Process your emotions\n\u2022 Journal about your feelings\n\u2022 Talk to friends or a therapist\n\u2022 Allow yourself to grieve the relationship\n\n3. Focus on self-improvement\n\u2022 Exercise regularly\n\u2022 Pick up new hobbies\n\u2022 Set personal goals\n\u2022 Practice self-care\n\n4. Stay busy\n\u2022 Spend time with friends and family\n\u2022 Try new activities\n\u2022 Work on professional development\n\n5. Practice mindfulness\n\u2022 Meditation\n\u2022 Deep breathing exercises\n\u2022 Redirect negative thoughts when they occur\n\n6. Avoid dwelling on the past\n\u2022 Don't romanticize the relationship\n\u2022 Recognize why it ended\n\u2022 Accept that it's over\n\n7. Consider professional help\n\u2022 Therapy can provide coping strategies\n\u2022 Help process complex emotions\n\u2022 Provide objective perspective\n\n8. Give yourself time\n\u2022 Healing isn't linear\n\u2022 Be patient with yourself\n\u2022 Understand that moving on takes time\n\nRemember, healing is a process, and it's okay to have difficult moments. Stay positive and focus on your personal growth.",
